<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="450" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 295.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-31"><hi rend="italic">October,</hi> 31, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I acknowledge the receipt of your despatch
                            of the 6th instant, No. 181, acquainting me with the gratifying manner
                            in which the French press comment upon the course of the President, and
                            our treatment of the rebel loan question.</p>
                        <p>I give you my thanks for your thoughtfulness.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>